_ref-8\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Chandler, 2002, p.18.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-9\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Berger, 2012, p.9.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-10\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-10\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Berger, 2012, p.9.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-11\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-11\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Cobley &amp; Jansz, 1997, p.4.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-12\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-12\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"> Chandler, 2002, p.18.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-13\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-13\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"> Cobley &amp; Jansz, 1997, p.4.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-14\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-14\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Berger, 2012, p.10.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Signified_and_signifier&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Ferdinand de Saussure (1959). <i>Course in General Linguistics</i>. New York: McGraw-Hill.</li>\n<li>Cobley, Paul &amp; Jansz, Litza (1997). <i>Introducing Semiotics</i>, Maryland: National Bookworm Inc.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Daniel_Chandler\" title=\"Daniel Chandler\">Chandler, Daniel</a> (2017). <i>Semiotics: The Basics</i>, New York: Routledge</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Arthur_Asa_Berger\" title=\"Arthur Asa Berger\">Berger, Arthur Asa</a> (2012). <i>Media Analysis Techniques</i>. Beverly Hills: Sage Publicati